         <entry xml:id="istrateltis-dlgenr"
            type="mainEntry"
            xml:lang="en"
            prev="#"
            next="#"
            source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">איסטרטלטיס</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾysṭrṭlṭys</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic">isṭratelṭis</pron>
               <gramGrp>
                  <gram type="pos">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen">m.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa">איסטרטליט</orth>
                  <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb">ʾysṭrṭlyṭ</orth>
                  <pron notation="rabbinic">isṭraṭliṭ</pron>
               </form>
               <form type="inflected">
                  <orth type="inflected" xml:lang="jpa">איסטרטילטין</orth>
                  <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb">ʾysṭrṭlṭyn</orth>
                  <pron notation="rabbinic">isṭratelṭin</pron>
                  <gramGrp>
                     <gram type="num">pl.</gram>
                  </gramGrp>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="istrateltis-dlgenr-1">
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>military officer, governor</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="la">
                  <quote>dux exercitus</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <quote>στρατηλατής</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>אמר ר' יהודה בר' סימון בשר ודם תולין לו אנקליטון מדוכס לאיפרכוס מאיפרכוס 
                     <app>
                        <lem>לאיסטרטלטיס</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#Vat2">לאיסטרטילוס</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Vat1">לאיסטרטילטיס</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#K">לאיסטרטילו</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#V">לאסטרטליטוס</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox1">לאיסטרטליס</rdg>
                        <rdg wit ="#Ox2">לאסטרליטוס</rdg>
                     </app>
                         ואת בשביל שאין לך מי יתלה לך אנקליטון לא תעשה משפט</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">49,9</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 511: 1</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אנקליטון</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דוכס</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">איפרכוס</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>R. Yehuda be-R. Simon said: (Abraham pleaded thus:) ‘Even in the case of a human judge, an appeal can be made from the commander to the prefect and from the prefect to the governor; but you, because no appeal can be made from your judgment, will you not do justly? (cf. Freedman / Simon I 429)</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">Yalq 83 [I 374: 82]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">לאסטרטליטי</term>)</note>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>למה הדבר דומה למלך בשר ודם שנכנס למדינה ונכנסו עמו דוכסים ואיפרכים ואסרטילטין אף על פי שכולם נכנסים בפילי אחת אלא כל אחד ואחד שורה לפי כבודו</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">96 (Vat 1)</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">III 1237: 8</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">איפרכים</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">פילי</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>What does it resemble? A human king who entered the province together with commanders, prefects and governors. Although they all entered through the same gate, but every one lined up according to his honour.</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">LevR Meṣoraʿ 18,1</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">ואיסטרטיוטין</term>); <bibl type="ancient">LevR (Margulies) Meṣoraʿ 18,1 [I 396: 5]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">ואיסטראטיאוטין</term>); <bibl type="ancient">KohR 12,1</bibl>; <bibl type="ancient">MHG Gen Wa-yeḥi 47,29 [II 802]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">ואסטרולגין</term>)</note>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>גדולה זו יוון, ר' סימון אמר מלכות יוון הייתה מעמדת ק"כ דוכסים וק"כ איפרכין וק"כ 
                     <app>
                        <lem>איסטרטלין</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#L">איסטרטלטון</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#V">אסטרטליטין</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#K">איסטרוטולוטין</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Vat1">איסטרטולין</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Vat2">איסטראטיליטין</rdg>
                     </app>
                  </quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">44,17</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 440: 1</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דוכסים</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">איפרכין</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>Great (Gen 15,12) refers to Greece. R. Simon said: The Kingdom of Greece set up one hundred and twenty commanders, one hundred and twenty prefects, one hundred and twenty governors. (cf. Freedman / Simon I 373)</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">Yalq 77 [I 308: 88]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">איסטרדיוטין</term>); <bibl type="ancient">LevR Shemini 13,5</bibl>; <bibl type="ancient">LeqT Gen 15,12 [35b]</bibl></note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <note>Widespread in the Rabb. Lit., variously spelled (and corrupted). See <bibl type="modern">AC I 176a</bibl>; <bibl type="modern">Levy I 122b</bibl>; <bibl type="modern">Krauss, LW II 84b-85a</bibl>; <bibl type="modern">Jastrow I 92ab</bibl>. For the reading in the parallels for <bibl type="ancient">III 1237: 8</bibl> in <bibl type="ancient">LerR</bibl> see <term xml:lang="jpa">אסטרטיוט</term> <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾsṭrṭywṭ</term> (from Gr. <term xml:lang="jpa">στρατιώτης</term>), <bibl type="modern">Krauss, LW II 84ab</bibl> (not in <bibl type="ancient">GenR</bibl>). Cf. Syr. <term xml:lang="syc">ܐܣܛܪܛܝܠܛܝܣ</term> <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾsṭrṭylṭys</term> (<bibl type="modern">Sokoloff, SL 71b</bibl>). Cf. <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="istartelis-ys.html">איסטרטלטיס</ref> Yalq.</note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl>
                  <title>Sokoloff, DJPA</title>
                  <citedRange>27b-28a</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
